	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=3650&mid=10288043363933>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=3650&mid=10288043363933>Faithstones make manastoning viable in Kunark+later</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=3650&mid=10288043363933#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Aug 8th 7:09 AM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=41286><span id=Scholar>Niccy</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>19 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.16]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Delicious as this item is, one downside has always been that it only works in the 'old world' - ie not in the planes, Kunark, Velious, Luclin. So for xping to 60 and beyond, it's really been the preserve of druids and wizards, who can bind in the expansion zone where they want to fight, port back to the old world to stone, and gate back to hunt again.<br><br>BUT there now exist player-made items called Faithstones (for clerics) and Spiritstones (for shaman) which have right-click 30 second cast self gates to home temple. A cleric or shaman with a portstone and a manastone can now:<br><br>Bind in an expansion zone near where they want to hunt<br>Hunt till oom<br>Portstone back to their temple (old world!)<br>Stone up to fm<br>Gate back to their bind point, and continue the hunt.<br><br>Both shaman and clerics can now get massive value from a manastone - I don't know enough about shaman spells/gear to comment on how good this is, but for a cleric with Donal's Arms (right click max 200hp heal) or other manafree healing item, or even just good old Complete Heal, this is FANTASTIC.<br><br>If you are a cleric and you wanna solo a bit, there are a fair few undead in Luclin who would hate to make your acquaintance, and with a manastone and a portstone, there's nothing to stop you!<br></p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
